# {{ .input_project_name }}

AI agent project deployed as a Databricks App. Generated by [AgentOps Stacks](https://github.com/sdonohoo-db/agentops-stacks).

## Setup

### 1. Install your agent framework

```bash
uv run setup
```

Select an agent template from the menu. This pulls the latest agent code from [databricks/app-templates](https://github.com/databricks/app-templates).

### 2. Configure workspace targets

Edit `databricks.yml` and set the `host:` URL for each target (dev, staging, prod, test). Set Unity Catalog catalog and schema names as needed.

### 3. Validate and deploy

```bash
databricks bundle validate -t dev
databricks bundle deploy -t dev
```

## Local Development

```bash
uv sync                    # install dependencies
uv run start-server        # start agent server on port 8000
uv run start-app           # start agent server + chat UI
```

## Project Layout

| Path | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `databricks.yml` | Bundle config — variables, targets, resource includes |
| `app.yaml` | Databricks App definition — start command, env vars |
| `agent_server/` | Agent code — `@invoke`/`@stream` handlers |
| `resources/` | DAB resource YAML — Databricks App definition |
| `scripts/` | Setup and local dev scripts |

## Deployment Targets

| Target | Catalog | Eval Threshold | Trigger |
|--------|---------|---------------|---------|
| dev | dev | relaxed | manual |
| staging | staging | strict | merge to main |
| prod | prod | strict | merge to release |
| test | test | relaxed | PR validation |

## Key Commands

```bash
databricks bundle validate -t dev       # check bundle config
databricks bundle deploy -t dev         # deploy all resources
databricks bundle run agent_development_job -t dev  # run agent dev + eval
```
